body:
Hi folks,

Sorry, this is not an exciting code contribution... but since I had to read the documentation anyways, I decided to fix whatever problems caught my attention in the process.

I tried to make my changes modular, so if you don't like something, just drop the corresponding patch.

HTH and thanks for working on Cython,

--Yury.

comment_data.body: python_exc.PyErr_NoMemory is used because it does't try to allocate more memory (whereas rais MemoryError does)
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -2,11 +2,13 @@ cimport cqueue
 cimport python_exc
 
 cdef class Queue:
+
     cdef cqueue.Queue* _c_queue
+
     def __cinit__(self):
         self._c_queue = cqueue.queue_new()
         if self._c_queue is NULL:
-            python_exc.PyErr_NoMemory()

comment_data.body:
Hi Robert,

In the documentation, it says:

> In the specific case of a MemoryError, creating a new exception instance in order to raise it may actually fail because we are running out of memory. Luckily, CPython provides a C-API function PyErr_NoMemory() that safely raises the right exception for us. Since version 0.14.1, Cython automatically substitutes this C-API call whenever you write raise MemoryError or raise MemoryError(). If you use an older version, you have to cimport the C-API function from the standard package cpython.exc and call it directly.

Did I misunderstand something? If yes, I can revert these changes.

Z.

comment_data.body: You're totally right, I forgot about that. Fixed.

commit.message: Fix some internal and external links in the documentation
Introduce more consistent capitalization of Python, Cython and NumPy
Prefer the use of C++ style pointer declarations (char *c -> char* c)
Fix broken code samples (indent, spaces, failing doctest)
Update code samples to use newer Cython / Python syntax
Fix various typos in the documentation
Fix one instance of code highlighting
